categories.title: Recent Pull Requests in the Eliza Repository

content.text:
Several pull requests have been submitted to the elizaOS/eliza repository, introducing new features and fixing existing issues:

- Documentation has been added for deploying Eliza to a Trusted Execution Environment (TEE) with the Oasis ROFL app (PR #4334)
- Path parameter routes for plugins have been enabled (PR #4335)
- A fix for Hapi types issue has been implemented (PR #4333)
- Gaimin AI has been added as a new AI Model Provider (PR #4343)
- A feature to skip displaying the banner if not UTF-8 has been added (PR #4344)
- A fix for the 'agent not found' error after GUI creation has been implemented, along with resolving merge conflicts (PR #4337)
- The .gitignore file is now being properly copied from the plugin-starter (PR #4345)

categories.title: Recent GitHub Issues in the elizaOS/eliza Repository

content.text:
Three recent issues have been reported in the elizaOS/eliza GitHub repository:

1. Issue #4336: A user named eduardoPauloPanstein reported problems with the Quickstart documentation.

2. Issue #4346: User UD1sto encountered an error when attempting to send a message without providing the ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, resulting in an error message stating "x-api-key header is required".

3. Issue #4342: User cxp-13 reported that all installation attempts for the plugin @elizaos/plugin-solana failed.

These issues suggest ongoing challenges with documentation clarity, API key requirements, and plugin installation processes in the eliza project.

The elizaos/eliza repository showed increased activity between April 22-24, 2025. From April 22-23, there were 2 new PRs with 1 merged, 1 new issue, and 7 active contributors. Activity increased the following day (April 23-24) with 7 new PRs (1 merged), 3 new issues, and the number of active contributors doubled to 14.
